`docs/` is project-level reference material consumed by agents and contributors, not source code: it explains why the system is built the way it is (DECISIONS.md), tracks what's broken or missing (STATUS.md / status.json), and specifies a not-yet-built lint crate (DYLINT_RULES.md).

STATUS.md and status.json are two views of the same backlog — status.json is the editable source of truth, STATUS.md is its generated, sorted rendering, and both must be edited only via `ctx-status`, never by hand. They currently agree on the same set of high-impact blockers: no validation gate on summarizer output, the Layer 3 auditor wired but never invoked, and prompt-vs-summary drift going undetected. Any change to one's task schema or format must be reflected in the generator that produces the other.

DYLINT_RULES.md describes lint rules that don't exist yet but that overlap two live scripts (`rationale_check.py`, `cycle_check.sh`); those scripts are meant to be superseded, not duplicated, whenever the corresponding dylint rule ships — a fact worth checking before editing either script or the spec.

DECISIONS.md is independent of the other three: it's an append-only historical record, never regenerated or reconciled against status/backlog state, and is the place to check before treating any architectural choice described elsewhere in `docs/` as arbitrary.